label: FGS222
info_overview:
Remotely Controlled Relay Switch of Fibaro System is designed to operate in a wall switch box or in locations where the control of an electric device (up to 3kW) is needed.
It is also possible to send a signal to any system that is to be integrated with Fibaro system.
info_inclusion: Add Fibaro Switch to the network by pushing three times key no. 1 or push-button B located inside the housing of the device. For toggle switch perform 3 position changes.
info_exclusion: Remove Fibaro Switch from the network by pushing three times key no. 1 or push-button B located inside the housing of the device. For toggle switch perform 3 position changes.
category_description: Any device attached to the wall that controls a binary status of something, for ex. a light switch

parameters.label: Override OFF-delay
parameters.overview: If Parameter 4 or 5 states an auto off period, this parameter enable the possibility to turn off the relay with a button push. Default value 0 disallow turn off with a button push during the auto off interval.

options.label: Manual override disabled
options.overview: Manual override disabled. After single button push the relay turns on and automatically turns off after specified time

options.label: Manual override enabled.
options.overview: Manual override enabled. After single button push the relay turns on and automatically turns off after specified time. Another button push turns the relay off immediately

parameters.description: Auto off relay 1 after set time, in 100ms increments (default: 0 - off)

parameters.description: Auto off relay 2 after set time, in 100ms increments (default: 0 - off)

options.overview: Commands are sent when device is turned off. Enabling device does not send control commands. Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command, dimmers memorize the last saved state (e.g. 50% brightness).
